From: ChatDBG Pro bench
Subject: [inject] weaken used-counter bound in inflate_table

Flip the `used < ENOUGH` guard in inflate_table()'s root-code loop
from strict-less-than to less-than-or-equal. That lets `used` step
exactly one slot past the end of the work/table array on any input
that needs a non-trivial Huffman code table.

NOTE: line numbers are approximate vs. v1.3.1. Step 4 re-bases this
before `git apply`.

---
 inftrees.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/inftrees.c b/inftrees.c
--- a/inftrees.c
+++ b/inftrees.c
@@ inflate_table
-            if (type == LENS && used >= ENOUGH_LENS)
+            if (type == LENS && used > ENOUGH_LENS)
                 return 1;
-            if (type == DISTS && used >= ENOUGH_DISTS)
+            if (type == DISTS && used > ENOUGH_DISTS)
                 return 1;
